[00:15.522]You needn't be so rude about it, my wife answered, as she looked at herself in the mirror. | “你没必要这么粗鲁，”我妻子看着镜子里的自己回答道。
[00:23.162]I sat down on one of those modern chairs with holes in it and waited. | 我坐在一把带洞的现代椅子上，等着。
[00:29.622]We had been in the hat shop for half an hour, and my wife was still in front of the mirror. | 我们已经在帽子店里待了半小时，我妻子仍然在镜子前。
[00:37.662]We mustn't buy things we don't need, I remarked suddenly. | “我们不应该买我们不需要的东西，”我突然说道。
[00:43.432]I regretted saying it almost at once. | 我几乎立刻就后悔说了那句话。
[00:48.382]You needn't have said that, my wife answered. | “你没必要说那句话，”我妻子回答道。
[00:51.982]I need not remind you of that terrible tie you bought yesterday. | 我没必要提醒你昨天买的那条糟糕的领带。
[00:58.552]I find it beautiful, I said. | “我觉得它很漂亮，”我说。
[01:01.782]A man can never have too many ties. | 男人永远不嫌领带多。
[01:06.122]And a woman can't have too many hats, she answered. | “女人也永远不嫌帽子多，”她回答道。
